Install Armbian Bionic image by downloading the latest Bionic version for the Cubox-i platform from armbian.
Use your favorite image writer to write image to microsd. On first boot the image will expand itself.
Follow Armbian instruction to get the image ready for use.

# sudo apt-get update ; sudo apt-get -y dist-upgrade ; sudo apt-get -y install git
# sudo useradd -m pi -s /bin/bash
# echo "pi ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL" | sudo tee /etc/sudoers.d/pi
# sudo chmod 0440 /etc/sudoer.d/pi
# sudo su - pi -c "git clone https://github.com/firewalla/firewalla.git"
# sudo su - pi -c "cd firewalla ; ./buildraw"
